onside (with)
Homonym Number:
Word Class:adjective
Sense Number:
Definition:in good with, in the good books of, on the right side of (someone)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:cf. offside with
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1945 at least It's best to keep onside with the boss. (probably from Rugby Football term <i>(keep)onside, associated with prob.</i> older expressions as <i>keep on the right side of, ... the side one's bread's buttered on </i> etc.)
